<subSubSection pageId="41" pageNumber="42" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="41.[151,1436,151,402]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,327,226,252]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Remarks:</emphasis>
An open median cell is only present in species in a few polycentropodid genera of the diagnostic genus clusters with simple wing venation, like 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Banks" authorityYear="1913" box="[835,949,264,289]" class="Insecta" family="Polycentropodidae" genus="Cyrnellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[835,949,264,289]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Cyrnellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Neboiss" authorityYear="1982" box="[964,1123,264,289]" class="Insecta" family="Polycentropodidae" genus="Adectophylax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[964,1123,264,289]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Adectophylax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ross" authorityYear="1938" box="[1140,1259,264,289]" class="Insecta" family="Polycentropodidae" genus="Cernotina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1140,1259,264,289]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Cernotina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1274,1428,264,289]" class="Insecta" family="Polycentropodidae" genus="Pahamunaya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1274,1428,264,289]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Pahamunaya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Neboiss, A." box="[151,330,301,327]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" pagination="191 - 205" refId="ref29413" refString="Neboiss, A. (1994) A review of the genus Paranyctiophylax Tsuda from Sulawesi, Papua New Guinea and Northern Australia (Trichoptera: Polycentropodidae). Memoirs of the Museum of Victoria, 54, 191 - 205." type="journal article" year="1994">Neboiss (1994)</bibRefCitation>
has found 3 
<taxonomicName authority="" box="[480,869,301,327]" class="Insecta" family="Polycentropodidae" genus="Nyctiophylax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Paranyctiophylax">
<emphasis box="[480,634,301,326]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Nyctiophylax</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[652,860,301,326]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Paranyctiophylax</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
species from 
<collectingCountry box="[1032,1139,301,327]" name="Australia" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Australia</collectingCountry>
and recently 
<bibRefCitation author="Johanson, K. A. &amp; Ward, J. B." pageId="41" pageNumber="42" pagination="11 - 47" refId="ref28253" refString="Johanson, K. A. &amp; Ward, J. B. (2009) Description of twenty-one new Polyplectropus species from New Caledonia (Trichoptera: Polycentropodidae). Annales de la SociZtZ entomologique de France, 45 (1), 11 - 47." type="journal article" year="2009">Johanson &amp; Ward (2009)</bibRefCitation>
have found 4 new 
<taxonomicName box="[522,790,338,364]" class="Insecta" family="Polycentropodidae" genus="Polyplectropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[522,698,338,363]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Polyplectropus</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[862,1043,338,364]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
with an open median cell in each forewing.
</paragraph>
